result.execSummary:
Jeffrey C Koehler was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jeffrey C Koehler was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Granting defendant's extradition to the State of IL

1:21 PM Prosecuting attorney Brenda L. Yaskal and Intern Hunter Johnson in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jeffrey C Koehler in court, in custody from the Columbia County Jail by video w/Atty Claire Edwards. Court addresses the extradition to the State of IL, Atty Edwards states defendant wishes to waive extradition, defendant agrees, signs extradition paperwork, Court grants defendant's extradition to the State of IL, Court orders defendant to be held w/out bond awaiting the State of IL officials, 1:24 P.M.
State of Illinois Warrant of Arrest filed by DA's office
